        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-7",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 1,
            "start": 75,
            "end": 75
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "知其白，守其黑，大白然後乃得。",
          "source": "cham"
        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-8",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 1,
            "start": 75,
            "end": 75
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "廣德不盈，廓然無形，不可滿也。",
          "source": "cham"
        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-9",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 1,
            "start": 75,
            "end": 75
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "偷，匹也。建德者，因物自然，不立不施，故若偷匹。",
          "source": "cham"
        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-10",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 1,
            "start": 75,
            "end": 75
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "質真者，不矜其真，故渝。",
          "source": "cham"
        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-11",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 0,
            "start": 69,
            "end": 70
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "方而不割，故無隅也。",
          "source": "cham"
        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-12",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 1,
            "start": 75,
            "end": 75
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "大器成天下不持全別，故必晚成也。",
          "source": "cham"
        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-13",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 0,
            "start": 81,
            "end": 82
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "聽之不聞名曰希，不可得聞之音也。有聲則有分，有分則不宮而商矣，分則不能統眾，故有聲者非大音也。",
          "source": "cham"
        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-14",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 1,
            "start": 75,
            "end": 75
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "有形則有分，有分者不溫則炎，不炎則寒。故象而形者，非大象。",
          "source": "cham"
        },
        {
          "id": "wangbi-15",
          "range": {
            "type": "range",
            "scope": "verse",
            "verseIndex": 2,
            "start": 0,
            "end": 10
          },
          "kind": "commentary",
          "text": "凡此諸善，皆是道之所成也。在象則為大象，而大象無形。在音則為大音，而大音希聲。物以之成而不見其成形，故隱而無名也。貸之非唯供其乏而已，一貸之則足以永終其德，故曰善貸也。成之不如機匠之裁，無物而不濟其形，故曰善成。",
          "source": "cham"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "source": {
    "textRef": "laozi-boshu",
    "relation": "section"
  }
}